ying All of Israel: David Ben-Gurion and the Book of Joshua -- tWho Is a Marrano?: Reflections on Modern Jewish Identity -- tThe Authors -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis volume takes a fresh view of the role representations of the past play in the construction of Jewish identity. Its central theme is that the study of how Jews construct the past can help in interpreting how they understand the nature of their Jewishness. The individual chapters illuminate the ways in which Jews responded to and made use of the past. If Jews’ choices of what to include, emphasize, omit, and invent in their representation of the past is a fundamental variable, then this volume contributes to the creation of a more nuanced approach to the construction of the histories of Jews and their thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCollective memory. 0aJewish diaspora. 0aJewsxHistory. 0aJewsxIdentity. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh1 aAdelman, Howard Tzvi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnctil, Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaader, Benjamin M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBell, Dean Phillip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCohn, Naftali S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiTommaso, Lorenzo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDiamond, James A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldscheider, Calvin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHavrelock, Rachel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLapidus, Steven, econtributor.